On Monday 17 July 2006 20:53, Andreas Mohr wrote:
> (a "continue" simply continue:s the loop without checking the loop condition
> at the bottom, right?)
I don't think so. Test it. This is no infinite loop:
int main(void)
{
        int i = 0;
        do {
                i++;
                continue;
        } while (i < 1000);
}
